# ERP Frontend – Project Context

This workspace is **avalon-ng** (ERP frontend): Angular 17, PrimeNG 17, TypeScript 5.2. Main app lives under `src/app/`.

## Tech stack

- **Angular 17** (standalone-friendly; some NgModules still used). Style: **SCSS**. Prefix: **app**.
- **PrimeNG** for UI (p-button, p-table, p-dialog, p-inputText, p-dropdown, etc.).
- **@ngx-translate** for i18n; keys in `src/assets/i18n/en.json` and `ar.json`.
- **Auth:** `AuthGuard` in `core/Guards/auth.guard.ts`; auth routes under `/auth` (login, 2FA, reset-password, etc.).

## App structure

- **`core/`** – Guards, interceptors, shared services, landing, notfound.
- **`layout/`** – Main shell: `AppLayoutComponent`, breadcrumb, sidebar (routes under this are protected).
- **`Shared/`** – Reusable UI (e.g. table-loading-spinner, erp-variables).
- **`modules/`** – Feature modules, lazy-loaded via `app-routing.module.ts`:
  - **dashboard** – `/`
  - **summary** – `/summary`
  - **system-administration** – `/system-administration` (erp-modules, erp-functions)
  - **entity-administration** – `/entity-administration` (entities, roles, user-accounts, entity-groups, workflows, entity-storage-management)
  - **document-control** – `/document-control` (file system, SSM, ESM, storage content)
  - **finance-accounting** – `/financials` (e.g. invoices)
  - **auth** – `/auth` (no layout, no guard)

## Conventions

- Prefer **simple, junior-friendly** Angular; avoid over-engineering and heavy RxJS.
- User-visible text in templates must use the **translate** pipe and keys in both `en.json` and `ar.json` (see rule **i18n-translations**).
- File-system / document-control features: follow **Docs/storage-management-file-system-api.md** (see rule **storage-file-system-api**).

When starting a new task, use this context to locate the right module, routing, and existing patterns.
